This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of crowd counting and density map estimation from images. The use of deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The mention of datasets and their importance in the success of recent methods suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the discussion of the merits and drawbacks of existing approaches and identification of promising avenues of research suggests that it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
